Summary: Maxima Symbolic Computation Program
Name: maxima
Version: @VERSION@
Release: 1
License: GPL
Group: Development/Languages
URL: http://maxima.sourceforge.net
Source0: %{name}-%{version}.tar.gz
BuildRoot: %{_tmppath}/%{name}-%{version}-buildroot

%description

Maxima is a full symbolic computation program.  It is full featured
doing symbolic manipulation of polynomials, matrices, rational
functions, integration, Todd-coxeter, graphing, bigfloats.  It has a
symbolic debugger source level debugger for maxima code.  Maxima is
based on the original Macsyma developed at MIT in the 1970's.  It is
quite reliable, and has good garbage collection, and no memory leaks.
It comes with hundreds of self tests.

%package clisp
Summary: Maxima compiled with clisp
Group: Development/Languages
Requires: clisp maxima
%description clisp
Maxima compiled with clisp.

%package cmucl
Summary: Maxima compiled with CMUCL
Group: Development/Languages
Requires: cmucl maxima
%description cmucl
Maxima compiled with CMUCL.

%package gcl
Summary: Maxima compiled with GCL
Group: Development/Languages
Requires: maxima
%description gcl
Maxima compiled with Gnu Common Lisp.

%prep
%setup -q
%configure --enable-clisp --enable-cmucl --enable-gcl

%build
make

%install
rm -rf $RPM_BUILD_ROOT
%makeinstall

%post
/sbin/install-info %{_infodir}/maxima.info.gz %{_infodir}/dir

%postun
/sbin/install-info --delete %{_infodir}/maxima.info.gz %{_infodir}/dir

%clean
rm -rf $RPM_BUILD_ROOT

%files
%defattr(-,root,root,-)
/usr/share/maxima/%{version}/*
/usr/libexec/maxima/%{version}
/usr/share/info/*.gz
/usr/share/man/man1/maxima.1.gz
/usr/bin/maxima
/usr/bin/xmaxima
%files clisp
/usr/lib/maxima/%{version}/binary-clisp/*
%files cmucl
/usr/lib/maxima/%{version}/binary-cmucl/*
%files gcl
/usr/lib/maxima/%{version}/binary-gcl/*

%doc


